cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a novel RNN architecture for natural language processing tasks, specifically language modeling and sentence completion. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses in-depth analysis of linguistic dimensions captured by the RMN, indicating a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the second likely sub-category. The use of RNNs and the proposed architecture also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for sentence completion, indicating a possible focus on computer vision and image processing, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as a less likely but still possible sub-category. Finally, the use of memory networks in the proposed architecture suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category.
